'''Pachri''' a di [[siramik]] matiirial we mekop pachriwier,<ref>'Pottery Science: materials, process and products.' Allen Dinsdale. Ellis Horwood Limited, 1986.</ref> we mieja taip ingkluud [[oerdnwier]], [[stuonwier]] ah [[puoslen]]. Di plies we soch kaina wier mek kaal ''pachri''. Pachri azwel refa tu di aat ar kraaf a di pata ar di manifakcha a pachri.<ref>[http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/pottery/ Merriam-Webster.com], akses 2010-09-04</ref><ref>'An Introduction To The Technology Of Pottery. 2nd edition. Paul Rado. Institute Of Ceramics & Pergamon Press, 1988</ref> Dikshineri definishan a simpli abjek mek outa klie we faya.<ref>[http://www.oed.com/view/Entry/148928?redirectedFrom=pottery#eid Pottery, meaning 3, mass noun], Oxford English Dictionary, Oxford University Press, 2015</ref> Di definishan a ''pachri'' yuuz bai di Amoerkan Sasayati fi Testin ah Matiirial (American Society for Testing and Materials, ASTM) a "aal siramik wier we faya ah we kantien klie wen ifaam, exsepm teknikal, schrokcharal, ah rifrakchri prodok."<ref>'Standard Terminology Of Ceramic Whitewares And Related Products.' ASTM C 242–01 (2007.) ''ASTM International''.</ref>

Pachri arijiniet bifuo di [[Niolitik Revaluushan|Niolitik]] piiriad, wid siramik abjek laka di [[Gravetian]] kolcha [[Viinos a Dolni Vestoniche]] (Venus of Dolní Věstonice) figariin we eh-diskova ina di [[Chek Ripoblik]] ah diet bak tu 29,000–25,000 BKE,<ref name=Venus>[http://www.uh.edu/engines/epi359.htm/ "No. 359: The Dolni Vestonice Ceramics"]. Uh.edu. 1989-11-24. Richriiv 2010-09-04.</ref> ah pachri vesl we eh-diskova ina Jiangshii, [[Chaina]], we diet bak tu 18,000 BKE.  Hoerli Niolitik pachri eh-fain ina plies laka Jomon, [[Japan]] (10,500 BC),<ref name=Jomon>[http://discovermagazine.com/1998/jun/japaneseroots1455/ "Japanese Roots"] Diamond, Jared (June 1998). Discover (Discover Media LLC). Richriiv 2010-07-10</ref> di [[Rosha|Roshan Faar Iis]] (14,000 BC),<ref name=fareastrussia> 'AMS 14C Age Of The Earliest Pottery From The Russian Far East; 1996-2002.' Derevianko A.P., Kuzmin Y.V., Burr G.S., Jull A.J.T., Kim J.C. Nuclear Instruments And Methods In Physics Research. B223-224 (2004) 735-739.</ref> Sob-Sa'aaran [[Afrika]] ah [[Sout Amoerka]].

